# Rows/Each -- a <ul><each>...<li> list (rows nested inside a <ul>, no
# per-row box: docs/ctml.md S:S14) alongside a top-level <each> of <div id=
# "todo-{{row.index}}"> rows, which DOES record one box per row because
# each div reaches the block walker directly, not through the list path.
# A trailing Data re-drive on the unrelated scalar list.title proves the
# row sequence -- fixed at Rows-build time -- survives a re-drive untouched
# (Rows itself cannot re-drive mid-tape, only Data can -- see doc.go).

Source rows.ctml
Set Width 80
Data list.title "Today"
Rows todos 3

Expect Text "Today"
Expect Text "Row 1"
Expect Text "Row 2"
Expect Text "Row 3"
Expect Box todo-list
Expect Box todo-0
Expect Box todo-1
Expect Box todo-2
Expect Fits

# Re-drive: only the scalar title changes; the row sequence is untouched.
Data list.title "Archive"
Expect Text "Archive"
Expect NotText "Today"
Expect Text "Row 1"
Expect Text "Row 3"
